{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843618876,"sessionID":"ses_2877918f6ffezvgoFvhl65AcnO","part":{"id":"prt_d78872b60001DczIlo9qAoXD4s","messageID":"msg_d788711220011yGq4BvQ5qefcs","sessionID":"ses_2877918f6ffezvgoFvhl65AcnO","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_d7f66e1b726d493b96c714a9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement a Sandbox creation handler in `pkg/workloadmanager` that provides unified APIs for creating and managing sandbox environments based on AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter Kubernetes resources. The handler exposes high-level sandbox operations through the existing HTTP service framework.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: The WorkloadManager module currently exposes low-level CRUD operations for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources through the HTTP service framework (AR-004). However, users and external systems often need a higher-level abstraction that encapsulates the complexity of setting up a complete sandbox environment with proper configuration, dependencies, and lifecycle management.\n12: \n13: ### Goal\n14: \n15: Provide a production-ready Sandbox creation handler that:\n16: - Offers unified, high-level APIs for sandbox environment creation\n17: - Supports multiple sandbox types (AgentRuntime-based, CodeInterpreter-based)\n18: - Handles resource dependency management and initialization sequencing\n19: - Provides sandbox lifecycle management (create, destroy, status, scaling)\n20: \n21: ### Value\n22: - Simplifies sandbox provisioning for end users\n23: - Abstracts away Kubernetes resource complexity\n24: - Enables sandbox templates and presets for common use cases\n25: - Provides a clean separation between sandbox operations and low-level resource management\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## Scope\n30: \n31: ### In-Scope\n32: \n33: | Deliverable | Description |\n34: |-------------|-------------|\n35: | Sandbox CRD/Model | Domain model representing sandbox configuration and state |\n36: | Sandbox Manager | Core logic for sandbox creation, deletion, and lifecycle management |\n37: | Sandbox Handlers | HTTP handlers for sandbox REST APIs |\n38: | Template System | Support for sandbox templates with predefined configurations |\n39: | Dependency Management | Handle resource dependencies and initialization order |\n40: \n41: ### API Endpoints\n42: \n43: #### Sandbox Management\n44: | Method | Path | Description |\n45: |--------|------|-------------|\n46: | POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes` | Create a new sandbox |\n47: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes` | List all sandboxes |\n48: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}` | Get sandbox details |\n49: | DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}` | Delete sandbox |\n50: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}/status` | Get sandbox status |\n51: | PATCH | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}/scale` | Scale sandbox resources |\n52: | POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}/restart` | Restart sandbox |\n53: \n54: #### Sandbox Templates\n55: | Method | Path | Description |\n56: |--------|------|-------------|\n57: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxtemplates` | List sandbox templates |\n58: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxtemplates/{name}` | Get template details |\n59: | POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxtemplates` | Create a template |\n60: \n61: ### Code Structure\n62: \n63: ```\n64: pkg/workloadmanager/\n65: ├── server.go                    # HTTP server (existing)\n66: ├── service.go                   # WorkloadManager interface (existing)\n67: ├── types.go                     # API types (existing)\n68: ├── client.go                    # Kubernetes client (existing)\n69: ├── sandbox/\n70: │   ├── manager.go               # Sandbox manager implementation\n71: │   ├── model.go                 # Sandbox domain model\n72: │   ├── handler.go               # HTTP handlers for sandbox APIs\n73: │   ├── template.go              # Template system\n74: │   └── template_handler.go      # Template HTTP handlers\n75: └── config/\n76:     └── config.go                # Configuration types\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ### Out-of-Scope\n80: - Container runtime implementation (handled by AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter)\n81: - Network policy management (future enhancement)\n82: - Persistent storage provisioning (future enhancement)\n83: - Multi-cluster sandbox management (future enhancement)\n84: - Sandbox monitoring and alerting (separate observability module)\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## Impact Analysis\n89: \n90: ### Dependencies\n91: \n92: | Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n93: |------------|--------|---------|\n94: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go | local | Kubernetes typed client for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter |\n95: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager | local | Existing WorkloadManager service |\n96: | k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime | ^1.34 | Object serialization |\n97: | k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1 | ^1.34 | metav1 types |\n98: \n99: ### Upstream Dependencies\n100: \n101: - **AR-004 WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework** — Provides the HTTP server and client integration\n102: - **AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter CRDs** — Underlying Kubernetes resources managed by sandboxes\n103: \n104: ### Downstream Consumers\n105: \n106: 1. **User-facing CLIs** — Simplified commands for sandbox management\n107: 2. **IDE integrations** — Create sandboxes for development environments\n108: 3. **CI/CD pipelines** - Ephemeral sandboxes for testing\n109: 4. **Multi-tenant platforms** - Isolated execution environments\n110: \n111: ### Risks\n112: \n113: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n114: |------|----------|------------|\n115: | Resource orphaning | High | Finalizers and cleanup handlers |\n116: | Template injection | Medium | Input validation and schema validation |\n117: | Concurrent operations | Medium | Optimistic locking with resourceVersion |\n118: | Cascading deletions | Medium | Explicit dependency tracking |\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ## Alternatives Considered\n123: \n124: ### Option 1: Direct AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter Usage (Selected)\n125: \n126: **Approach**: Extend the existing WorkloadManager with sandbox-specific abstractions that wrap AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources.\n127: \n128: **Pros**:\n129: - Reuses existing infrastructure from AR-004\n130: - Clear separation between low-level CRUD and high-level sandbox operations\n131: - Gradual implementation following the existing patterns\n132: - Type-safe with strong Kubernetes integration\n133: \n134: **Cons**:\n135: - Requires additional abstraction layer\n136: - May have slight overhead compared to direct access\n137: \n138: **Decision**: Selected — provides the best balance of simplicity and functionality.\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ### Option 2: Separate Sandbox Operator\n143: \n144: **Approach**: Implement a full Kubernetes operator for Sandbox resources with custom resource definition.\n145: \n146: **Pros**:\n147: - Native Kubernetes reconciliation patterns\n148: - Automatic reconciliation on resource changes\n149: - Standard operator lifecycle management\n150: \n151: **Cons**:\n152: - Higher complexity and development time\n153: - Requires separate deployment and maintenance\n154: - Overkill for current requirements\n155: \n156: **Decision**: Rejected — can be considered as a future enhancement.\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ### Option 3: Generic Resource Proxy\n161: \n162: **Approach**: Implement a generic proxy that transforms arbitrary resource requests into Kubernetes operations.\n163: \n164: **Pros**:\n165: - Highly flexible\n166: - Supports any resource type\n167: \n168: **Cons**:\n169: - Loses type safety\n170: - Complex validation logic\n171: - Harder to maintain and debug\n172: \n173: **Decision**: Rejected —牺牲 type safety for marginal flexibility.\n174: \n175: ---\n176: \n177: ### Option 4: External Sandbox Service\n178: \n179: **Approach**: Implement sandbox management as a separate microservice.\n180: \n181: **Pros**:\n182: - Complete isolation from workload manager\n183: - Independent scaling and deployment\n184: - Technology flexibility\n185: \n186: **Cons**:\n187: - Additional infrastructure complexity\n188: - Network latency between services\n189: - Requires service discovery and load balancing\n190: \n191: **Decision**: Rejected — adds unnecessary operational complexity for current scale.\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ## Implementation Plan\n196: \n197: ### Phase 1: Core Model\n198: - [ ] Define `Sandbox` and `SandboxTemplate` domain models\n199: - [ ] Implement sandbox state machine (Pending, Running, Failed, Terminating)\n200: - [ ] Create validation logic for sandbox configurations\n201: \n202: ### Phase 2: Sandbox Manager\n203: - [ ] Implement `SandboxManager` interface\n204: - [ ] Create sandbox from AgentRuntime template\n205: - [ ] Create sandbox from CodeInterpreter template\n206: - [ ] Implement sandbox lifecycle operations (create, delete, restart, scale)\n207: - [ ] Add status aggregation from underlying resources\n208: \n209: ### Phase 3: HTTP Handlers\n210: - [ ] Add sandbox REST endpoints to server.go\n211: - [ ] Implement request/response mapping\n212: - [ ] Add watch support for sandbox status changes\n213: - [ ] Implement template management endpoints\n214: \n215: ### Phase 4: Template System\n216: - [ ] Implement template CRUD operations\n217: - [ ] Add template validation and defaults\n218: - [ ] Support template inheritance/composition\n219: \n220: ### Phase 5: Testing\n221: - [ ] Unit tests for sandbox manager\n222: - [ ] Integration tests with fake clientset\n223: - [ ] End-to-end tests with test Kubernetes cluster\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ## Acceptance Criteria\n228: \n229: - [ ] Sandbox creation creates appropriate AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter resource\n230: - [ ] Sandbox status reflects aggregated state of underlying resources\n231: - [ ] Sandbox deletion properly cleans up all dependent resources\n232: - [ ] Sandbox templates can be created, listed, and used\n233: - [ ] All sandbox operations are properly logged\n234: - [ ] Error cases return appropriate HTTP status codes\n235: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage for sandbox logic\n236: - [ ] Concurrent sandbox operations are handled correctly\n237: - [ ] Graceful shutdown properly terminates sandbox operations\n\n(End of file - total 237 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement a Sandbox creation handler in `pkg/workloadmanager` that provides unified APIs for creating and managing sandbox environments based on AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter Kubernetes resources. The handler exposes high-level sandbox operations through the existing HTTP service framework.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe WorkloadManager module currently exposes low-level CRUD operations for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources through the HTTP service framework (AR-004). However, users and external systems often need a higher-level abstraction that encapsulates the complexity of setting up a complete sandbox environment with proper configuration, dependencies, and lifecycle management.\n\n### Goal\n\nProvide a production-ready Sandbox creation handler that:\n- Offers unified, high-level APIs for sandbox environment creation\n- Supports multiple sandbox types (AgentRuntime-based, CodeInterpreter-based)\n- Handles resource dependency management and initialization sequencing\n- Provides sandbox lifecycle management (create, destroy, status, scaling)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775843618864,"end":1775843618874}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843618881,"sessionID":"ses_2877918f6ffezvgoFvhl65AcnO","part":{"id":"prt_d78871fe80010X6FNsnl7DrMkW","messageID":"msg_d788711220011yGq4BvQ5qefcs","sessionID":"ses_2877918f6ffezvgoFvhl65AcnO","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_ff9964f7a50f4981b7da9744","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management features in `pkg/workloadmanager`. This includes cleanup of expired sandboxes, graceful termination, force deletion, and lifecycle hooks.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-006\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Depends On**: AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器)\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Scenario: Sandbox Deletion\n18: \n19: ### AR-006-001: Delete Sandbox by SessionID\n20: \n21: - **GIVEN** an existing sandbox with known SessionID\n22: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{sessionId}`\n23: - **THEN** the handler SHALL locate the sandbox by SessionID\n24: - **AND** SHALL initiate Pod termination\n25: - **AND** SHALL clean up associated resources (services, configmaps)\n26: - **AND** SHALL remove the sandbox from the store\n27: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with deletion confirmation\n28: \n29: ### AR-006-002: Delete Sandbox by Name\n30: \n31: - **GIVEN** an existing sandbox with known name\n32: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/name/{name}`\n33: - **THEN** the handler SHALL locate the sandbox by name\n34: - **AND** SHALL perform the same cleanup as AR-006-001\n35: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n36: \n37: ### AR-006-003: Force Delete Sandbox\n38: \n39: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with terminating Pod that fails to stop gracefully (stuck in Terminating state > 5 minutes)\n40: - **WHEN** a DELETE request includes `gracePeriodSeconds=0` and `force=true`\n41: - **THEN** the handler SHALL forcefully delete the Pod using DeleteOptions\n42: - **AND** SHALL bypass finalizers if necessary\n43: - **AND** SHALL clean up all associated resources\n44: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n45: \n46: ### AR-006-004: Delete Non-existent Sandbox\n47: \n48: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n49: - **WHEN** a DELETE request targets a non-existent sandbox\n50: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n51: - **AND** SHALL include error message \"sandbox not found\"\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## Scenario: Graceful Shutdown\n56: \n57: ### AR-006-010: Graceful Termination with Draining\n58: \n59: - **GIVEN** a running sandbox with active connections\n60: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is received with `gracePeriodSeconds=30`\n61: - **THEN** the handler SHALL send SIGTERM to the sandbox process\n62: - **AND** SHALL wait for grace period before force termination\n63: - **AND** SHALL allow in-flight requests to complete\n64: - **AND** SHALL reject new requests during grace period\n65: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK only after termination completes or grace period expires\n66: \n67: ### AR-006-011: Pre-delete Hook\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with pre-delete lifecycle hook configured\n70: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is received\n71: - **THEN** the handler SHALL execute the pre-delete hook\n72: - **AND** SHALL wait for hook to complete (max 30 seconds)\n73: - **AND** SHALL proceed with deletion regardless of hook result\n74: - **AND** SHALL log hook execution status\n75: \n76: ### AR-006-012: Connection Draining\n77: \n78: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with active connections\n79: - **WHEN** graceful termination is initiated\n80: - **THEN** the handler SHALL stop routing new traffic to the sandbox\n81: - **AND** SHALL wait for existing connections to close (max grace period)\n82: - **AND** SHALL return \"draining\" status during the grace period\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## Scenario: TTL and Expiration\n87: \n88: ### AR-006-020: Sandbox TTL Enforcement\n89: \n90: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with TTL set to 1 hour\n91: - **WHEN** the sandbox exceeds its TTL\n92: - **THEN** the garbage collector SHALL automatically delete the sandbox\n93: - **AND** SHALL emit an event for TTL expiration\n94: - **AND** SHALL clean up all associated resources\n95: - **AND** SHALL log the expiration for auditing\n96: \n97: ### AR-006-021: Idle Timeout\n98: \n99: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with IdleTimeout set to 10 minutes\n100: - **WHEN** no requests are received for 10 minutes\n101: - **THEN** the garbage collector SHALL mark the sandbox as idle\n102: - **AND** SHALL terminate idle sandboxes based on idle timeout policy\n103: - **AND** SHALL support both immediate deletion and graceful draining for idle sandboxes\n104: \n105: ### AR-006-022: Max Lifetime\n106: \n107: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with MaxLifetime set to 24 hours\n108: - **WHEN** the sandbox exceeds MaxLifetime\n109: - **THEN** the garbage collector SHALL reject new requests\n110: - **AND** SHALL terminate the sandbox after current requests complete\n111: - **AND** SHALL ensure sandboxes do not run indefinitely\n112: \n113: ---\n114: \n115: ## Scenario: Batch Operations\n116: \n117: ### AR-006-030: Delete All Sandboxes in Namespace\n118: \n119: - **GIVEN** multiple sandbox instances in a namespace\n120: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes` with `deleteAll=true`\n121: - **THEN** the handler SHALL delete all sandboxes in the namespace\n122: - **AND** SHALL return the count of deleted sandboxes\n123: - **AND** SHALL support async deletion for large batches\n124: \n125: ### AR-006-031: Delete Sandboxes by Label Selector\n126: \n127: - **GIVEN** multiple sandbox instances with various labels\n128: - **WHEN** a DELETE request includes `labelSelector=app=foo`\n129: - **THEN** the handler SHALL delete only sandboxes matching the label selector\n130: - **AND** SHALL return the count of deleted sandboxes\n131: \n132: ### AR-006-032: Delete Stale Sandboxes\n133: \n134: - **GIVEN** sandboxes in \"Unknown\" or \"Failed\" state for > 1 hour\n135: - **WHEN** the garbage collector runs\n136: - **THEN** the handler SHALL identify stale sandboxes\n137: - **AND** SHALL automatically clean up stale sandboxes\n138: - **AND** SHALL emit events for stale sandbox cleanup\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ## Scenario: Lifecycle Events\n143: \n144: ### AR-006-040: Emit Deletion Event\n145: \n146: - **GIVEN** a sandbox is deleted\n147: - **THEN** the handler SHALL emit a Kubernetes Event\n148: - **AND** SHALL include deletion reason, initiated by, and timestamp\n149: \n150: ### AR-006-041: Webhook Notification on Deletion\n151: \n152: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with deletion webhook configured\n153: - **THEN** the handler SHALL send POST notification to the webhook URL\n154: - **AND** SHALL include sandbox metadata in the request body\n155: - **AND** SHALL retry up to 3 times on failure\n156: - **AND** SHALL proceed with deletion regardless of webhook response\n157: \n158: ### AR-006-042: Deletion Audit Log\n159: \n160: - **GIVEN** a sandbox deletion operation\n161: - **THEN** the handler SHALL log:\n162:   - Sandbox identifier (SessionID, name)\n163:   - Namespace\n164:   - Deletion reason (explicit, TTL, idle, stale)\n165:   - Initiator (user, system)\n166:   - Duration from deletion request to completion\n167:   - Resources cleaned up\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## Scenario: Resource Cleanup\n172: \n173: ### AR-006-050: Cleanup Associated Services\n174: \n175: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with associated Services\n176: - **WHEN** the sandbox is deleted\n177: - **THEN** the handler SHALL delete all Services owned by the sandbox\n178: - **AND** SHALL use ownerReference for automatic cleanup verification\n179: \n180: ### AR-006-051: Cleanup ConfigMaps and Secrets\n181: \n182: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with injected ConfigMaps or Secrets\n183: - **WHEN** the sandbox is deleted\n184: - **THEN** the handler SHALL delete ConfigMaps if marked for deletion\n185: - **AND** SHALL NOT delete Secrets (they may be shared)\n186: - **AND** SHALL log cleanup actions\n187: \n188: ### AR-006-052: Cleanup PVCs\n189: \n190: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with PVCs\n191: - **WHEN** the sandbox is deleted\n192: - **THEN** the handler SHALL handle PVC cleanup based on ReclaimPolicy\n193: - **AND** SHALL delete PVCs with ReclaimPolicy=Delete\n194: - **AND** SHALL retain PVCs with ReclaimPolicy=Retain\n195: \n196: ---\n197: \n198: ## Scenario: Error Handling\n199: \n200: ### AR-006-060: Deletion Failure Handling\n201: \n202: - **GIVEN** a sandbox deletion request\n203: - **WHEN** the Kubernetes API returns an error during deletion\n204: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return appropriate HTTP status code\n205: - **AND** SHALL include error message with cause details\n206: - **AND** SHALL log the error for debugging\n207: - **AND** SHALL retry deletion up to 3 times for transient errors\n208: \n209: ### AR-006-061: Orphaned Resource Cleanup\n210: \n211: - **GIVEN** a sandbox whose Pod was deleted externally\n212: - **WHEN** the garbage collector detects the orphan\n213: - **THEN** the handler SHALL clean up the sandbox record\n214: - **AND** SHALL clean up any orphaned Services or ConfigMaps\n215: - **AND** SHALL emit an event for orphan cleanup\n216: \n217: ### AR-006-062: Finalizer Handling\n218: \n219: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with finalizers\n220: - **WHEN** deletion is requested\n221: - **THEN** the handler SHALL execute all finalizers\n222: - **AND** SHALL remove finalizer only after successful execution\n223: - **AND** SHALL handle stuck finalizers with force deletion\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ## References\n228: \n229: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md`\n230: - Related AR: AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器)\n231: - Sandbox CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n232: - Garbage Collector: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n233: - API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n\n(End of file - total 233 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management features in `pkg/workloadmanager`. This includes cleanup of expired sandboxes, graceful termination, force deletion, and lifecycle hooks.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-006\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Depends On**: AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器)\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Sandbox Deletion\n\n### AR-006-001: Delete Sandbox by SessionID\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775843618859,"end":1775843618879}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843618884,"sessionID":"ses_2877918f6ffezvgoFvhl65AcnO","part":{"id":"prt_d788725ad001A6mVyobw9uTM4N","messageID":"msg_d788711220011yGq4BvQ5qefcs","sessionID":"ses_2877918f6ffezvgoFvhl65AcnO","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_bbe6d3c32ebb45c0bcd98f24","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-1 (Draft)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Deletion Handlers\n11: \n12: - [ ] **1.1** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` - Add handleSandboxDelete() handler for DELETE by SessionID\n13: - [ ] **1.2** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` - Add handleSandboxDeleteByName() handler for DELETE by name\n14: - [ ] **1.3** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` - Register DELETE routes: /v1/namespaces/{ns}/sandboxes/{sessionId}, /v1/namespaces/{ns}/sandboxes/name/{name}\n15: - [ ] **1.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/delete_options.go` - DeleteOptions struct with GracePeriodSeconds, Force, LabelSelector fields\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## Phase 2: Graceful Shutdown\n20: \n21: - [ ] **2.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/graceful_shutdown.go` - gracefulDeleter struct\n22: - [ ] **2.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/graceful_shutdown.go` - drainConnections() to stop routing new traffic\n23: - [ ] **2.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/graceful_shutdown.go` - waitForConnections() with timeout\n24: - [ ] **2.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/graceful_shutdown.go` - executePreDeleteHook() for lifecycle hooks\n25: - [ ] **2.5** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/graceful_shutdown.go` - sendSIGTERM() to container\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## Phase 3: TTL and Expiration\n30: \n31: - [ ] **3.1** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` - Add TTL check logic\n32: - [ ] **3.2** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` - Add idle timeout detection\n33: - [ ] **3.3** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` - Add MaxLifetime enforcement\n34: - [ ] **3.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/expiration.go` - isExpired() helper for TTL/Idle/MaxLifetime checks\n35: - [ ] **3.5** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` - Add DefaultTTL, DefaultIdleTimeout, DefaultMaxLifetime constants\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## Phase 4: Batch Operations\n40: \n41: - [ ] **4.1** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` - Add handleDeleteAllSandboxes() for namespace-wide deletion\n42: - [ ] **4.2** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` - Add handleDeleteByLabelSelector() for filtered deletion\n43: - [ ] **4.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/batch_delete.go` - deleteStaleSandboxes() for Unknown/Failed state cleanup\n44: - [ ] **4.4** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` - Register DELETE /v1/namespaces/{ns}/sandboxes with query params\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ## Phase 5: Lifecycle Events and Webhooks\n49: \n50: - [ ] **5.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_events.go` - emitDeletionEvent() using event recorder\n51: - [ ] **5.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_events.go` - sendDeletionWebhook() with retry logic\n52: - [ ] **5.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_events.go` - logDeletionAudit() for audit trail\n53: - [ ] **5.4** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` - Add WebhookConfig, AuditLogEntry types\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## Phase 6: Resource Cleanup\n58: \n59: - [ ] **6.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/resource_cleanup.go` - cleanupServices() to delete owned Services\n60: - [ ] **6.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/resource_cleanup.go` - cleanupConfigMaps() to delete owned ConfigMaps\n61: - [ ] **6.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/resource_cleanup.go` - cleanupPVCs() with ReclaimPolicy handling\n62: - [ ] **6.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/resource_cleanup.go` - cleanupOrphanedResources() for external deletions\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ## Phase 7: Error Handling\n67: \n68: - [ ] **7.1** Update error types in `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` - Add ErrSandboxNotFound, ErrDeletionFailed, ErrStaleFinalizer\n69: - [ ] **7.2** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` - Map error types to HTTP status codes\n70: - [ ] **7.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/retry.go` - retryDeletion() with exponential backoff\n71: - [ ] **7.4** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` - Add retry logic for failed deletions\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ## Phase 8: Integration with AR-005\n76: \n77: - [ ] **8.1** Integrate with sandbox_creator: Handle cleanup on creation failure (rollback)\n78: - [ ] **8.2** Integrate with store: Call DeleteSandbox(), GetSandbox() for deletion verification\n79: - [ ] **8.3** Integrate with k8s_client: Use dynamic client for deletion operations\n80: - [ ] **8.4** Ensure graceful shutdown integrates with existing informer watches\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ## Phase 9: Unit Tests\n85: \n86: - [ ] **9.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers_delete_test.go` - TestHandleSandboxDelete_Success\n87: - [ ] **9.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers_delete_test.go` - TestHandleSandboxDelete_NotFound\n88: - [ ] **9.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers_delete_test.go` - TestHandleSandboxDelete_Force\n89: - [ ] **9.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/graceful_shutdown_test.go` - TestDrainConnections\n90: - [ ] **9.5** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/graceful_shutdown_test.go` - TestExecutePreDeleteHook\n91: - [ ] **9.6** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` - TestTTLExpiration\n92: - [ ] **9.7** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` - TestIdleTimeout\n93: - [ ] **9.8** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/batch_delete_test.go` - TestDeleteAllInNamespace\n94: - [ ] **9.9** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/batch_delete_test.go` - TestDeleteByLabelSelector\n95: - [ ] **9.10** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_events_test.go` - TestEmitDeletionEvent\n96: - [ ] **9.11** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/resource_cleanup_test.go` - TestCleanupServices\n97: - [ ] **9.12** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/expiration_test.go` - TestIsExpired_TTL\n98: - [ ] **9.13** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/expiration_test.go` - TestIsExpired_IdleTimeout\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## Phase 10: Integration Tests\n103: \n104: - [ ] **10.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_delete_test.go` - E2E test for sandbox deletion\n105: - [ ] **10.2** Test graceful shutdown with active connections\n106: - [ ] **10.3** Test TTL expiration and cleanup\n107: - [ ] **10.4** Test batch deletion with 100+ sandboxes\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: ## Phase 11: Verification\n112: \n113: - [ ] **11.1** Run `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` - successful compilation\n114: - [ ] **11.2** Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` - all unit tests pass\n115: - [ ] **11.3** Run `go test -race ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` - no race conditions\n116: - [ ] **11.4** Run `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` - no issues\n117: - [ ] **11.5** Run `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` - linter passes\n118: - [ ] **11.6** Verify test coverage > 40% with `go test -coverprofile=coverage.out ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ## Dependencies\n123: \n124: | Task | Depends On |\n125: |------|------------|\n126: | Phase 1 | AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器) |\n127: | Phase 2 | Phase 1 (handlers) |\n128: | Phase 3 | Phase 1 (handlers) |\n129: | Phase 4 | Phase 1-3 |\n130: | Phase 5 | Phase 1 (handlers) |\n131: | Phase 6 | AR-005 (k8s_client, informers) |\n132: | Phase 7 | Phase 1 (types) |\n133: | Phase 8 | AR-005 (sandbox_creator, store, k8s_client) |\n134: | Phase 9 | Phase 1-8 (implementation complete) |\n135: | Phase 10 | Phase 9 (unit tests) |\n136: | Phase 11 | All phases |\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ## References\n141: \n142: - Design: `sandbox-orchestration/AR-006-sandbox-deletion-lifecycle/design.md`\n143: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md`\n144: - Related AR: AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器)\n\n(End of file - total 144 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Tasks\n\n**Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-1 (Draft)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Deletion Handlers\n\n- [ ] **1.1** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` - Add handleSandboxDelete() handler for DELETE by SessionID\n- [ ] **1.2** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` - Add handleSandboxDeleteByName() handler for DELETE by name\n- [ ] **1.3** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` - Register DELETE routes: /v1/namespaces/{ns}/sandboxes/{sessionId}, /v1/namespaces/{ns}/sandboxes/name/{name}\n- [ ] **1.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/delete_options.go` - DeleteOptions struct with GracePeriodSeconds, Force, LabelSelector fields\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Graceful Shutdown\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-006/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775843618863,"end":1775843618881}}}}
