{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843673096,"sessionID":"ses_2877918f6ffezvgoFvhl65AcnO","part":{"id":"prt_d78877cf6001peSf8sOetURHoY","messageID":"msg_d788773df001J1LeotkYyZBBRH","sessionID":"ses_2877918f6ffezvgoFvhl65AcnO","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_1e5dcb742d804cffaeda4035","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement sandbox deletion and lifecycle management features in `pkg/workloadmanager`, providing comprehensive control over sandbox termination, graceful shutdown, TTL/expiration handling, and resource cleanup. This extends the sandbox creation capabilities from AR-005 with complete lifecycle management.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nAR-005 provides sandbox creation capabilities, but production environments require robust deletion handling to:\n- Gracefully terminate active sandboxes without disrupting in-flight requests\n- Enforce TTL and idle timeout policies for resource optimization\n- Clean up associated Kubernetes resources (Services, ConfigMaps, PVCs)\n- Provide audit trails and lifecycle events for operational visibility\n\n### Goal\n\nProvide a production-ready sandbox deletion and lifecycle management system that:\n- Supports graceful termination with connection draining\n- Enforces TTL, idle timeout, and max lifetime policies\n- Handles batch deletion and label-based filtering\n- Emits lifecycle events and webhooks for external integrations\n- Properly cleans up all associated Kubernetes resources\n\n### Value\n- Prevents resource leaks through automated cleanup\n- Enables policy-driven sandbox lifecycle management\n- Provides operational auditability for compliance\n- Supports zero-downtime deployments through graceful shutdown\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| Deletion Handlers | HTTP handlers for DELETE by SessionID/name, force delete |\n| Graceful Shutdown | Connection draining, pre-delete hooks, SIGTERM handling |\n| TTL/Expiration | TTL enforcement, idle timeout, max lifetime garbage collection |\n| Batch Operations | Delete all in namespace, label selector deletion, stale cleanup |\n| Lifecycle Events | K8s events, webhooks, audit logging |\n| Resource Cleanup | Services, ConfigMaps, PVCs, orphaned resources |\n\n### API Endpoints\n\n#### Sandbox Deletion\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{sessionId}` | Delete sandbox by SessionID |\n| DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/name/{name}` | Delete sandbox by name |\n| DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes` | Delete all in namespace |\n| DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Delete AgentRuntime |\n| DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Delete CodeInterpreter |\n\n#### Query Parameters\n| Parameter | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| gracePeriodSeconds | int | Seconds to wait before force termination |\n| force | bool | Force deletion bypassing finalizers |\n| deleteAll | bool | Delete all sandboxes in namespace |\n| labelSelector | string | Label selector for filtered deletion |\n\n### Code Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── server.go                    # HTTP server (existing)\n├── service.go                   # WorkloadManager interface (existing)\n├── types.go                     # API types (existing)\n├── client.go                    # Kubernetes client (existing)\n├── handlers.go                  # Existing handlers + delete handlers\n├── delete_options.go            # DeleteOptions struct\n├── graceful_shutdown.go         # Graceful termination logic\n├── garbage_collector.go        # TTL/idle/maxLifetime enforcement\n├── expiration.go                # isExpired() helpers\n├── batch_delete.go              # Batch deletion operations\n├── lifecycle_events.go          # Event emission, webhooks, audit\n├── resource_cleanup.go          # Service/ConfigMap/PVC cleanup\n├── retry.go                     # Retry logic for failed deletions\n└── sandbox/\n    └── (from AR-005)\n```\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n- Sandbox scaling (AR-005)\n- Sandbox monitoring/alerting (separate observability module)\n- Multi-cluster deletion (future enhancement)\n- Sandbox migration between namespaces (future enhancement)\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n|------------|--------|---------|\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go | local | Kubernetes typed client |\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager | local | Existing WorkloadManager |\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1 | local | AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter types |\n| k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime | ^1.34 | Object serialization |\n| k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1 | ^1.34 | metav1 types |\n| k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes | ^1.34 | Kubernetes client |\n\n### Upstream Dependencies\n\n- **AR-005 (Sandbox 创建处理器)** — Provides sandbox creation and management foundation\n- **AR-004 WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework** — Provides HTTP server infrastructure\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **Garbage Collection Jobs** — Automated cleanup of expired/idle sandboxes\n2. **CI/CD Pipelines** — Ephemeral sandbox cleanup after tests\n3. **Operator Controllers** — Kubernetes-native lifecycle management\n4. **Monitoring Systems** — Lifecycle event consumption\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Resource orphaning | High | Finalizers, ownerReferences, cleanup verification |\n| Stuck terminating Pods | Medium | Force deletion with gracePeriodSeconds=0 |\n| Cascading failures | Medium | Retry with exponential backoff, error propagation |\n| Data loss | High | ReclaimPolicy handling for PVCs, confirmation for force delete |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: Direct Kubernetes Deletion (Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Implement deletion handlers that directly interact with Kubernetes API, using ownerReferences and finalizers for cleanup.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Native Kubernetes patterns\n- Leverages existing client-go infrastructure\n- Automatic cleanup through garbage collection\n- Well-understood failure modes\n\n**Cons**:\n- Requires understanding of K8s delete semantics\n- Limited control over graceful termination timing\n\n**Decision**: Selected — provides the best integration with Kubernetes ecosystem.\n\n---\n\n### Option 2: Sidecar-based Lifecycle Manager\n\n**Approach**: Deploy a sidecar container in each sandbox that handles lifecycle events.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Granular control over individual sandbox lifecycle\n- Isolation from workload manager\n\n**Cons**:\n- Additional resource overhead per sandbox\n- Complex sidecar communication\n- Overhead for current requirements\n\n**Decision**: Rejected — adds unnecessary complexity.\n\n---\n\n### Option 3: External Deletion Service\n\n**Approach**: Implement sandbox deletion as a separate microservice with its own API.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Independent scaling\n- Complete isolation\n\n**Cons**:\n- Additional infrastructure\n- Network latency\n- Duplicate logic with existing service\n\n**Decision**: Rejected — unnecessary operational complexity.\n\n---\n\n### Option 4: Operator Pattern with Custom CRD\n\n**Approach**: Implement a full Kubernetes operator for sandbox lifecycle.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Native reconciliation\n- Automatic retry and healing\n\n**Cons**:\n- Higher implementation complexity\n- Separate deployment\n- Overkill for current scale\n\n**Decision**: Rejected — can be considered as future enhancement when more advanced reconciliation is needed.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Deletion Handlers\n- [ ] Add handleSandboxDelete() for DELETE by SessionID\n- [ ] Add handleSandboxDeleteByName() for DELETE by name\n- [ ] Register DELETE routes in server.go\n- [ ] Implement DeleteOptions struct\n\n### Phase 2: Graceful Shutdown\n- [ ] Implement gracefulDeleter with drainConnections()\n- [ ] Implement waitForConnections() with timeout\n- [ ] Implement executePreDeleteHook()\n- [ ] Implement sendSIGTERM() to containers\n\n### Phase 3: TTL and Expiration\n- [ ] Update garbage_collector.go with TTL check\n- [ ] Add idle timeout detection\n- [ ] Add max lifetime enforcement\n- [ ] Implement isExpired() helper\n\n### Phase 4: Batch Operations\n- [ ] Implement handleDeleteAllSandboxes()\n- [ ] Implement handleDeleteByLabelSelector()\n- [ ] Implement deleteStaleSandboxes()\n\n### Phase 5: Lifecycle Events\n- [ ] Implement emitDeletionEvent() using event recorder\n- [ ] Implement sendDeletionWebhook() with retry\n- [ ] Implement logDeletionAudit()\n\n### Phase 6: Resource Cleanup\n- [ ] Implement cleanupServices()\n- [ ] Implement cleanupConfigMaps()\n- [ ] Implement cleanupPVCs() with ReclaimPolicy\n- [ ] Implement cleanupOrphanedResources()\n\n### Phase 7: Error Handling\n- [ ] Add ErrSandboxNotFound, ErrDeletionFailed error types\n- [ ] Map errors to HTTP status codes\n- [ ] Implement retryDeletion() with backoff\n\n### Phase 8: Testing\n- [ ] Unit tests for deletion handlers\n- [ ] Graceful shutdown tests\n- [ ] TTL/idle timeout tests\n- [ ] Batch deletion tests\n- [ ] Integration tests\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] DELETE by SessionID returns 200 OK and cleans up resources\n- [ ] DELETE by name returns 200 OK and cleans up resources\n- [ ] Force deletion bypasses finalizers when gracePeriodSeconds=0\n- [ ] DELETE non-existent sandbox returns 404 Not Found\n- [ ] Graceful termination waits for connections before force kill\n- [ ] Pre-delete hooks execute before deletion proceeds\n- [ ] TTL enforcement automatically deletes expired sandboxes\n- [ ] Idle timeout terminates inactive sandboxes\n- [ ] Batch deletion with label selectors works correctly\n- [ ] Associated Services/ConfigMaps are cleaned up\n- [ ] PVC cleanup respects ReclaimPolicy\n- [ ] Lifecycle events are emitted to Kubernetes\n- [ ] Webhooks are sent with retry on failure\n- [ ] Audit logs capture deletion details\n- [ ] Unit tests pass with >40% coverage","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/client/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go\">\nERROR [33:22] cannot use s.indexer.GetByKey(key) (value of type interface{}) as *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\".AgentRuntime value in assignment: need type assertion\nERROR [40:9] invalid operation: obj (variable of type *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\".AgentRuntime) is not an interface\nERROR [66:22] cannot use s.indexer.GetByKey(key) (value of type interface{}) as *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\".AgentRuntime value in assignment: need type assertion\nERROR [73:9] invalid operation: obj (variable of type *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\".AgentRuntime) is not an interface\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/client/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go\">\nERROR [33:22] cannot use s.indexer.GetByKey(key) (value of type interface{}) as *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\".CodeInterpreter value in assignment: need type assertion\nERROR [40:9] invalid operation: obj (variable of type *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\".CodeInterpreter) is not an interface\nERROR [66:22] cannot use s.indexer.GetByKey(key) (value of type interface{}) as *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\".CodeInterpre